    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-01T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-01T17:00:00-05:00" n="296"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d296">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/180</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJK1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-01T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 1, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">Stevens</persName>:</p>
                <p>About 120 men will be sent to Vladivostok locomotive shop. No trouble arranging
                    commissary and food for them. How do you <pb facs="0251" n="201" xml:id="pg_201"
                    /> suggest matter be handled for the twelve units of officers who we understand
                    will be scattered all over Russia? Difficult to get accommodations on Pacific
                    which may delay movement. Shall we send interpreters or will you provide them in
                    Russia? Answer Washington, <persName corresp="#p_FSM1">Felton</persName>.<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d296fn1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_FSM1">Samuel M. Felton</persName>, Director General of
                        Military Railways, War Department.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
